# Terraform Cloud Configuration Example
# This file shows how to configure Terraform Cloud for this workspace

# 1. Create a Terraform Cloud account at https://app.terraform.io
# 2. Create an organization (e.g., "jaimefrancosalazar")
# 3. Create a workspace named "stori-challenge-dev"
# 4. Configure the workspace settings:

# Workspace Settings:
# - Execution Mode: Remote
# - Terraform Version: >= 1.0
# - Working Directory: terraform/environments/dev

# Environment Variables (set in Terraform Cloud workspace):
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID        = <your-aws-access-key>
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY    = <your-aws-secret-key>
# AWS_DEFAULT_REGION       = us-east-2

# Terraform Variables (set in Terraform Cloud workspace):
# These override values in terraform.tfvars
# - aws_region              = "us-east-2"
# - project_name            = "stori-challenge"
# - alert_email             = "your-email@example.com"  (optional)
# - container_image         = "nginx:1.25-alpine"

# Version Control Settings (optional):
# - Connect to GitHub repository: jaimefrancosalazar/stori-take-home-challenge
# - VCS Branch: main
# - Automatic Run Triggering: enabled for changes in terraform/

# Notifications (optional):
# - Configure Slack/Email notifications for run status
# - Set up for: Plan changes, Apply completed, Apply errored

# Team Access:
# - Configure team permissions as needed
# - Recommended: Separate read/write access for different teams
